      <title>MECHANISMS AND MOTION</title>
      <para id="id1165295054286">Introduction</para>
      <para id="id2362624">What is a mechanism?</para>
      <list id="id7348292" list-type="bulleted">
        <item>In our everyday life we are surrounded by mechanisms. They help make our life easier in many ways. Most of the mechanisms you use are so familiar that you never think about them. Simple things like door handles, light switches, parts of a bicycle and a car are only a few examples. In the past, in old machines such as steam engines, the mechanisms were easy to see. Today they are hidden behind panels and covers. Mechanisms allow us to do simple things like switching on lights, running a bath and peddling up the hill easily on a bicycle. You will discover the uses of different mechanisms, as we look at them closer in this module.</item>
      </list>
