      <para id="id7990409"/>
      <para id="id1165292489343">Mechanisms and Motion</para>
      <list id="id1165296897394" list-type="bulleted">
        <item>Mechanisms can be used to change the speed, direction or force required to do something. Mechanisms may be able to help you but they cannot do it on their own. They need energy and someone or something to operate them. The energy that is used by a machine is called the input. The result of this energy input is called the output. A mechanism such as a bicycle can be explained with the diagram below.</item>
